caller_intent: The caller (Kathy) is concerned about her insurance policy (1214) being marked as 'cancellation status' despite sending a premium payment via check, and wants clarification on the status.
resolution_steps: Rachel confirms Kathy sent a check for the premium via mail.
Rachel asks for the date the check was mailed (Kathy says 'Sunday the 11th').
Rachel explains that the company's system (Cincinnati) may not have received the check yet, and advises waiting 1-2 days for processing.
knowledge_required: Understanding of check payment processing timelines
Policy cancellation rules for unpaid premiums
How to interpret carrier system statuses
summary: Kathy called to resolve confusion about her policy (1214) being marked as canceled after sending a check for premium payment. Rachel confirmed the check was mailed on 10/11 and explained the carrier may need more time to process it. The call ended with Rachel advising Kathy to wait 1-2 days for resolution.
